        public Drive.Revisions.Delete delete(java.lang.String fileId,
                            java.lang.String revisionId)
                              throws java.io.IOException
        Permanently deletes a revision. This method is only applicable to files with binary content in Drive. Create a request for the method "revisions.delete". This request holds the parameters needed by the drive server. After setting any optional parameters, call the AbstractGoogleClientRequest.execute() method to invoke the remote operation.
        Parameters:
        fileId - The ID of the file.
        revisionId - The ID of the revision.
